<p class="bg-wine-50 p-4 rounded-lg">Avoid pairing delicate whites with red meat—they'll disappear completely. Skip highly oaked Chardonnay, which clashes with beef's savory profile. Sweet wines create unpleasant contrasts, while excessively tannic young wines can overpower lighter preparations. Most importantly, avoid serving wines too warm—even reds should be slightly chilled (60-65°F) to maintain balance with hot food.</p>

